## Important Notes

- Be constructive, not destructive — focus on making the transcript better
- High severity issues: factual errors, major speaker inconsistencies
- Medium severity: awkward phrasing, pacing problems, missed content
- Low severity: minor style improvements, nitpicks
- The revised transcript should be a polished, production-ready version
- If the transcript is already excellent, say so and make minimal changes

